    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a study of the effect of consumer-directed financial incentives on completion of
      advance care planning among Medi-Cal patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Older adults receiving primary care from one of three clinics contracting with Partnership
      HealthPlan of California, a multi-county Medi-Cal managed care plan will be mass randomized
      to receiving educational materials regarding advance care planning with or without a
      financial reward for completing advance care planning.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
